The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Trio in net for loan dupe
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Trio in net for loan dupe
          A STAFF REPORTER                               
	Three persons were arrested on Monday from Bidhan Sarani and Shyampukur, in north Calcutta, for duping a person of Rs 41,000.        
	Ashish Das, an electronics goods dealer in Hedua, associate Pradip Bose and Parimal Chakrabarty, an employee of the shop, had duped Pradip Kumar Roy Chowdhury of Fern Road by offering a loan at low interest rates.         
	A probe revealed that the trio had duped five others to the tune of nearly Rs 85,000.                                                                                                                                                                          
